{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d24039d6-2a4e-4fe7-8222-94e9f7d95042","content":"In xUnit v3 with MTP, the VSTest filter syntax (`--filter`) is replaced by the `--filter` option using **MTP filter expressions**, which have different property names and operators.\n\n**Your old filter:**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**Translated for xUnit v3 + MTP:**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Trait[Category]=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n\n| VSTest syntax | MTP syntax |\n|---|---|\n| `&` (AND) | `and` |\n| `\\|` (OR) | `or` |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `Trait[Category]=Smoke` |\n| `~` (contains) | `~` (still works) |\n\nIn MTP, traits are accessed via `Trait[<name>]=<value>` rather than being top-level properties. The boolean operators become keywords (`and`, `or`, `not`) instead of symbols.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6f334895-5c21-4186-b28c-dd83804edd06","outputTokens":255,"requestId":"285D:3577AF:1590991:16FB3D3:6A046049"},"id":"d258ecfa-d6c7-45c2-a8f0-258571dfd224","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:28:18.359Z","parentId":"e38d52ac-86e0-4042-a020-e977dd5a50ea"}
